  "local_port": 41380,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which are the best books for bank exam?",
  "response": "Preparing for bank exams requires a good selection of study materials that cover the necessary subjects in depth. Here are some highly recommended books for various bank exams, like IBPS, SBI, and others:\n\n### General Awareness and Current Affairs:\n1. **\"Manorama Yearbook\" or \"India Year Book\"** - Comprehensive for current affairs and general knowledge.\n2. **\"Banking Awareness\" by Kiran Prakashan** - Focused on banking terms and principles.\n3. **\"Monthly Current Affairs Magazines\" (like Pratiyogita Darpan)** - Regular updates on current events.\n\n### Quantitative Aptitude:\n1. **\"Quantitative Aptitude for Competitive Examinations\" by R.S. Aggarwal** - Good for basic concepts and practice.\n2. **\"Fast Track Objective Arithmetic\" by Rajesh Verma** - Focuses on shortcuts and speed calculations.\n\n### Reasoning Ability:\n1. **\"Analytical Reasoning\" by M.K. Pandey** - Covers a wide range of reasoning topics.\n2. **\"A Modern Approach to Verbal and Non-Verbal Reasoning\" by R.S. Aggarwal** - Excellent for various reasoning types.\n\n### English Language:\n1. **\"Objective General English\" by S.P. Bakshi** - Comprehensive coverage of English grammar and usage.\n2. **\"Word Power Made Easy\" by Norman Lewis** - Helpful for vocabulary enhancement.\n\n### Computer Awareness:\n1. **\"Computer Awareness\" by K. Ramesh** - Covers all fundamental computer knowledge and terminologies.\n2. **\"Objective Computer Awareness\" by P. K. Gupta** - A helpful guide focusing specifically on the banking exam requirements.\n\n### Descriptive Writing:\n1. **\"High School English Grammar and Composition\" by Wren & Martin** - Great for improving writing skills.\n2. **Practice essays and formal letter writing** - Regular practice can improve descriptive writing skills.\n\n### Mock Tests and Practice Papers:\n1. **Online platforms such as Gradeup, Oliveboard, and Testbook** - Offer mock tests and previous years' papers.\n2. **\"Bank Exam Guide\" by Disha Experts** - Contains practice questions and mock exams.\n\n### Subject-Specific Books:\n- **\"Bank PO and Clerk Exam\" by Arihant Experts** - Comprehensive coverage of all subjects.\n- **\"IBPS Bank Clerk Exam\" by Kiran Prakashan** - Specifically focused preparation for IBPS Clerk.\n\n### Study Tips:\n1. **Time Management:** Create a study schedule to cover all topics.\n2. **Revision:** Regularly revise concepts to ensure retention.\n3. **Practice:** Solve previous year\u2019s question papers and take mock tests.\n\nSelect books that best cater to your learning style and understand that consistent practice and revision are key to success in bank exams.",
